HOSOKAWA ALPINE Aktiengesellschaft Film Extrusion Division
Hosokawa Alpine is a globally leading and innovative machine and plant manufacturer with headquarters in Augsburg and a branch office in Leingarten. The company also has several subsidiaries in Germany and abroad. Hosokawa Alpine''s core competence lies in the Mechanical Processing division, which manufactures machines and systems for the processing of powders, granulates and bulk materials, and in the Film Extrusion division, which manufactures systems for the production and finishing of blown films. Since 1987, the company has been a wholly owned subsidiary of the Japanese Hosokawa Micron Corporation.

The Film Extrusion Division is one of the world''s leading suppliers of machinery for film production. From consulting, planning and development to installation, the company accompanies all project steps of its customers. HOSOKAWA ALPINE blown film lines and monoaxial film stretching lines are used for numerous applications and convince by high efficiency as well as flexibility. Customers from all over the world use our machines to produce fresh produce and industrial packaging.

In addition to mono-layer lines, the company also produces multi-layer lines. Starting with 3-layer lines, the current standard, through 5-layer lines to 7-, 9- and 11-layer blown films. This results in demand-oriented packaging with optimum mechanical and optical properties.
